## đź”‘ Key Takeaways
1. **Pool the C# Logic, not just the Prefab:** If a game entity requires a C# class to run its logic (like an MVC Controller), pool the C# class wrapping the GameObject, not just the GameObject. This prevents the `new` keyword from triggering the Garbage Collector.
2. **Never Trust `defaultCapacity`:** Unity's Object Pool needs to be forcefully exercised during loading screens using the "Hoard & Return" loop if you want to avoid mid-game stutter.
3. **Clean Up Your Toys:** Always reset properties (Health, Timers, Trail Renderers, NavMesh Destinations) either right before they go back in the box (`actionOnRelease`) or the exact moment you take them out (`actionOnGet`).
